


Install


Using system libgtk and Python virtualenv:


0. install gtk+3

sudo apt-get install gtk+3-dev

1. create and activate a new virtual env

# Firstly you should always use the latest stable Python virtualenv
# and always verify it's gpg signature before using!

./virtualenv-x.y.z/virtualenv.py --system-site-packages virtenv-hidden-tahoe/
. virtenv-hidden-tahoe/bin/activate


2. install

pip install git+https://github.com/david415/hidden-tahoe-backup.git


# or if you have a local git clone of the repo then:

cd /home/amnesia/Persistent/projects/hidden-tahoe-backup
pip install .

